The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 London, April 2 (PTI): A 25-year-old Indian was stabbed to death in a racial attack in Ilford, Essex, police said on Monday. Jaspreet Singh, from Punjab, was stabbed when he and a friend were waiting for a bus on Saturday morning. 

 A 19-year-old unemployed youth, identified as Kamuzu Munroe of Ilford, was charged with the murder and produced before the Redbridge magistrates court.

 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has granted bail to Amardeep Singh Gill, who was sentenced to four years in prison by Delhi High Court in the Jessica Lal murder case. Gill, convicted for destroying evidence, had to furnish a personal bond of Rs 25,000 and a surety of the same amount.

 Madurai (PTI):Police seized 86 detonators and 65 gelatine sticks during a raid at Chemmanipatti, about 30 km from here, on Monday. The police said the explosives were found in a garden, whose owner has been taken into custody. 

 Dubai (PTI): A heavy fine will be imposed on expatriates in Saudi Arabia if their family members visiting them overstay their visa period. A two-month grace period will be given from April 3 to June 1 for the expatriates and companies to send their visitors back before the imposition of the new law. 

 Mandi (PTI): The Himachal Pradesh wildlife wing has decided to shut down the Rewalsar zoo near here and relocate the 100-odd animals cramped in a 5-hectare area to other parks. The decision follows a Central Zoo Authority directive of 2002 against ill-maintained and small zoos.

 Salem (PTI): A 15-year-old boy drowned in the swimming pool of a private residential school on Sunday. Selvendran, a Class IX student, was swimming with his friends when he drowned, police said. He was taken taken to hospital were he was declared brought dead.




